As the Winter Olympics in Pyeongchang came to a close on Sunday, there were murmurings of intent to bring the two Koreas closer together after the games had ceased. The colorful closing ceremony saw a US delegation that included US President Donald Trump's daughter Ivanka seated only a few seats from North Korean General Kim Yong Chol, who has been accused of masterminding attacks on the South Korean military. Send  Facebook   Twitter   Google+   Whatsapp   
